ZH: 我在外地工作，感觉很孤单。
EN: I feel lonely working in a different city.

ZH: 他离开了家乡，远离了亲人，过上了孤单的生活。
EN: He left his hometown, separated from his family, and started a lonely life.

ZH: 她一个人住在这个城市，常常感到孤单。
EN: She lives alone in this city and often feels lonely.

ZH: 在这个空旷的房间里，我感到非常孤单。
EN: I feel extremely lonely in this empty room.

ZH: 孤单的时候，最想念的是家人的陪伴。
EN: When feeling lonely, what I miss the most is the company of family.

ZH: 他一个人度过了整个周末，感到非常孤单。
EN: He spent the entire weekend alone and felt very lonely.

ZH: 她的朋友都结婚了，她感到越来越孤单。
EN: Her friends are all married, and she feels increasingly lonely.

ZH: 在这个陌生的城市里，她经历了很长时间的孤单。
EN: She experienced a long period of loneliness in this unfamiliar city.

ZH: 没有人理解他的感受，他感到非常孤单。
EN: No one understands his feelings, and he feels very lonely.

ZH: 刚来到新学校的时候，我感到非常孤单。
EN: I felt very lonely when I first arrived at the new school.

ZH: 他害怕独处，因为他觉得很孤单。
EN: He is afraid of being alone because he feels lonely.

ZH: 每当夜晚来临，孤单的感觉就会更强烈。
EN: Whenever night falls, the feeling of loneliness becomes stronger.

ZH: 跟朋友聚会的时候，我不再感到孤单。
EN: I don't feel lonely anymore when I gather with friends.

ZH: 孤单的日子里，我只能寻找自己的寄托。
EN: In the days of loneliness, I can only seek solace within myself.

ZH: 他因为工作太忙，很多时间都是孤单一个人。
EN: Because of his busy work, he spends a lot of time alone.

ZH: 孤单的时候，我会听音乐来舒缓心情。
EN: When feeling lonely, I listen to music to ease my mood.

ZH: 每当心情低落的时候，我都会感到孤单。
EN: Whenever my mood is low, I feel lonely.

ZH: 当生活中缺少爱和陪伴，很容易感到孤单。
EN: It's easy to feel lonely when there is a lack of love and companionship in life.

ZH: 被人遗忘的感觉让我感到非常孤单。
EN: The feeling of being forgotten makes me feel extremely lonely.

ZH: 孤单的日子里，有时候跟陌生人聊天也能带来些安慰。
EN: In days of loneliness, sometimes chatting with strangers can bring some comfort.
